# Prisma Rules

- Keep schema names and relation fields explicit and consistent across models.
- Prefer additive, reversible migrations; avoid destructive migration patterns unless explicitly approved.
- Validate nullable and optional behavior at the service boundary, not only at query call sites.
- Select only required fields in queries to reduce payload size and avoid over-fetching.
- Keep transactional logic explicit for multi-step writes.
- Never expose raw database errors directly to end users.
